headline: Colgate Stock Jumps After Earnings. Why the Shares Can Keep Investors Smiling.
summary: Colgate-Palmolive  beat earnings and revenue expectations in the fourth quarter, helping the stock to continue its strong start to the 2026.  The household product leader reported adjusted earnings of 95 cents a share, as revenue rose 5.8% from a year ago to $5.23 billion.  Wall Street had anticipated earnings of 91 cents a share on revenue of $5.13 billion, according to analysts polled by FactSet.

headline: 3 Mid-Cap Stocks with Open Questions
summary: Mid-cap stocks often strike the right balance between having proven business models and market opportunities that can support $100 billion corporations. However, they face intense competition from scaled industry giants and can be disrupted by new innovative players vying for a slice of the pie.
